Rating: 4
Following the advice of "A Cook from Mount Pleasant" in another review, I made this a second time using Garam Masala that I had made and stored some months before. I let the works simmer for a few hours to let all the flavors do their thing, including some salt and about a tablespoon of pumpkin pie spice with Cardamom (similar to Trader Joe's mix). Brilliant-fantastic-and the guests this second time liked it even better than the first time I made it last fall. It became their favorite dish then, and it's become a greater favorite now.

