Rating: 4
This was terrific. Amazing way to use leftover trukey, without feeling like you're having turkey again. I was halving the recipe, until I was adding the spices, and I forgot, so I ended up with double spices in the final product, but it wasn't too strong at all, it was delicious. I also used fresh bell pepper instead of tomatoes with bell pepper, and currents instead of raisins because that's what I had. I will make this year after year.

Rating: 4
I love this recipe! I'm making it right now -between Thanksgiving and Christmas- with a cooked turkey leg from the store. And I'll probably make it again with Christmas leftovers. My favorite part is telling people what's in it (pumpkin pie spice, chili powder, vinegar?!?) then letting them taste it. Their faces really light up! Everyone loves it.

Rating: 4
I made this recipe last night, and have to tell you that you MUST try it. It is easy, quick and very tasty! The green pepper I added was a wonderful addition. Also, the "leftover" turkey I had was from a cooked (purchased that way) turkey breast roast. I was afraid it would be dry, so cut the pieces about 3/4" to 1" instead of the 1/2 as called for in the recipe. It was not dry. Therefore, I can make this again without having to cook a whole turkey to get the leftovers! Believe me, I will!

